# HD Masale — Environment Variables

## Backend (FastAPI)
- `DATABASE_URL`: SQLAlchemy connection string (sqlite or postgres)
- `SECRET_KEY`: Long random string for JWT signing
- `ALGORITHM`: Usually HS256
- `ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES`: JWT TTL
- `FRONTEND_URL`: CORS origin for Next.js
- `ADMIN_LAT`: Latitude of your warehouse (e.g. 19.9975)
- `ADMIN_LNG`: Longitude of your warehouse (e.g. 73.7898)
- `UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL`: For distance calculation caching
- `UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN`: For distance calculation caching

## Frontend (Next.js)
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL`: Backend URL (e.g. http://localhost:8000)
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY`: API key with Maps JS, Places, and Geocoding enabled
- `UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL`: (Optional on frontend, used if sharing client)
- `UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN`: (Optional on frontend, used if sharing client)
